Hey there! To automate the selection of all checkboxes on a page and then save them when you click a "Save" button, you can use JavaScript to do the job. Here’s a simple way to do it:

1. **Select all checkboxes**: You can use `document.querySelectorAll` to select all checkboxes.
2. **Check each checkbox**: Loop through the selected checkboxes and check them.
3. **Handle the Save button click**: Add an event listener to your "Save" button to trigger the checkbox checking.

Here's a quick example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Checkbox Automation</title>
</head>
<body>

<input type="checkbox" id="checkbox1"> Checkbox 1<br>
<input type="checkbox" id="checkbox2"> Checkbox 2<br>
<input type="checkbox" id="checkbox3"> Checkbox 3<br>

<button id="saveButton">Save</button>

<script>
    // Select all checkboxes
    const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

    // Function to check all checkboxes
    function checkAllCheckboxes() {
        checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => {
            checkbox.checked = true;
        });
    }

    // Get the Save button
    const saveButton = document.getElementById('saveButton');

    // Add event listener to the Save button
    saveButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
        checkAllCheckboxes();
        console.log("All checkboxes checked!");
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How It Works:
- The script selects all checkboxes on the page using `document.querySelectorAll`.
- It defines a function `checkAllCheckboxes` that loops through the selected checkboxes and sets their `checked` property to `true`.
- An event listener is added to the "Save" button. When the button is clicked, it calls `checkAllCheckboxes`.

This way, when you click the "Save" button, all checkboxes will be automatically checked. You can adjust this code to fit your specific needs, like saving the state somewhere or doing something else with the checked values.

